Sec. 58.038. TAX STATUS OF BONDS. The bonds issued by the
authority, any transaction relating to the bonds, and any profits
made in the sale of the bonds are free from taxation by the state or
by any city, county, special district, or other political subdivision
of the state; provided that this section does not exempt the owner
of any property financed under this chapter from any ad valorem,
sales, use, excise, or other tax levied by the state or any political
Statute text rendered on: 8/6/2022

